"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130091","Department for Transport","false","2019-06-10","<p>The Government recognises that climate change is one of the most urgent and pressing challenges we face and we are working to ensure the UK takes a leading role in tackling it.</p><p> </p><p>In December 2018 the Government published a green paper consultation for a new aviation strategy, ‘Aviation 2050 – The future of UK aviation’. It commits the Government to ensure that the aviation sector plays its part by limiting greenhouse gas emissions and contributing to achieving the UK’s domestic and international climate change obligations.</p><p> </p><p>The green paper also includes a proposal that “<em>planning applications for capacity growth provide a full assessment of emissions, drawing on all feasible, cost-effective measures to limit their climate impact and demonstrate that their project will not have a material impact on the Government’s ability to meet its carbon reduction targets</em>”. However, this proposal is still subject to consultation and is not yet the Government’s policy. The consultation closes on 20 June.</p><p> </p><p>On 2 May the Committee on Climate Change (CCC) published advice to government, recommending the UK legislates for a 2050 net zero greenhouse gas emissions target. We await aviation specific advice from the CCC and will take this into consideration in the development of Aviation 2050, which is due to be published later this year.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis",,"2019-06-10T15:34:16.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130091/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130091/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-06-05","Regional Airports: Air Pollution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 4 June 2019 to Question 256996 on regional airports: air pollution, what criteria his Department uses to define material impact in determining how a project affects the Government's ability to meet its carbon reductions target.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","260619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130092","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-06-10","<p>Although the Government has not undertaken this specific assessment, we closely monitor trends in bird populations. These trends have long been considered to provide a good indication of the broad state of our wildlife.</p><p> </p><p>In November last year, the Government published <em>Wild Bird Populations in England, 1970 to 2017</em>. Overall, this showed that the combined all-species index has changed little compared with around 45 years ago. However, there was much variation in numbers between species, with some species increasing and some species decreasing.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2019-06-10T10:46:00.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130092/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130092/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130092/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-06-05","Hedges and Ditches","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment he has made of the effect of netting hedgerows on nesting birds.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","260592"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130093","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-06-10","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the reply given to the hon. Member for Hornsey and Wood Green, Catherine West, on 15 April 2019 to PQ 242911.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2019-06-10T10:32:05.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130093/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130093/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130093/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-06-05","Hedges and Ditches","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps he is taking to protect and conserve hedgerows.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","260593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130094","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-06-10","<p>There are no plans to review regulations governing the netting of bird nesting places, as it is enforcement that is required rather than new regulations.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2019-06-10T16:18:13.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130094/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130094/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130094/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-06-05","Hedges and Ditches","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to amend the Wildlife and Countryside Act 1981 to include stronger regulation on the netting of hedgerows.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","260594"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130095","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-06-10","<p>The Ministry of Defence has concluded phase one of the radar review following internal and external engagement. This has helped us develop our understanding of the factors we will need to consider for the future developments of radar capability. We are considering how we take this review forward, which will be informed by the forthcoming Defence Science Expert Committee RF sensing report.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2019-06-10T15:25:55.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130095/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130095/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130095/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-06-05","Radar","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when her Department plans to conclude the radar technology baseline review; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","260595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130096","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-06-10","<p>The Ministry of Defence has concluded phase one of the radar review following internal and external engagement. This has helped us develop our understanding of the factors we will need to consider in the future development of Radar capability post 2030. We are considering how we take this review forward, which will be informed by the forthcoming Defence Science Expert Committee RF sensing report. We will of course consult with industry in any next steps and this would include the offshore wind industry through the Aviation Management Board, where appropriate to do so.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2019-06-10T15:25:07.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130096/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130096/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1130096/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-06-05","Radar: Wind Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether her Department plans to consult the offshore wind industry for the radar technology baseline review.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","260596"
